dc_title_s: LiDAR-Derived Countywide 60-cm Bare Earth DEM (m) for Polk County, WI 2022
dc_description_s: This data represents a LiDAR-derived 60-cm Bare Earth Digital Elevation Model (DEM) for Polk County, Wisconsin in 2022. This dataset has elevation values in meters and is in the WTM coordinate system: EPSG 3071. A DEM represents the bare-Earth surface, removing all natural and built features.
dc_creator_sm: Wisconsin Department of Administration - Geographic Information Office
uw_supplemental_s: This lidar data dataset was created by the WisconsinView Partners (WVP) – the WI Department of Administration’s Geographic Information Office in collaboration with the UW-Madison WisconsinView repository. Original lidar data in tiled format from federal or local county/city lidar projects were used to create countywide mosaics of datasets such as DEMS, Intensity images, and DSMs in various projections and coordinate systems.  For detailed metadata please visit: https://web.s3.wisc.edu/wsco-wisconsinview/lidar/Polk/Polk_2022_3DEP_Delivery/Metadata/Metadata.zip
